"""
================================================================================
Foundation Initializer  —  Inception-Layer Module
ai2agi Architecture  |  Ai70000, Ltd.  |  Alex Osterneck, CLA, MSCS, MSIT
================================================================================

PURPOSE:
    Standalone inception-layer module. Runs ONCE at system startup, BEFORE
    any episode, BEFORE any tensor is generated. Seeds MQ, TB, and HKS from
    the NIV Scripture corpus as the foundational input layer of G_enhanced.

    This module does not alter any existing component. It initializes the
    input foundations that G_enhanced's sub-modules draw from. All subsequent
    tensor generation flows from these consecrated foundations.

GATEWAY:
    MQ  — Moral Quotient training signal source
    TB  — Time-Binding semantic memory (SymbolicMemory)
    HKS — Hierarchical Knowledge Structure root

SCHEMA (per ai2agi 2023–2025 convention):
    1. Textual Description
    2. Computation Notation
    3. Python Implementation

POSITION IN PIPELINE:
    foundation_initializer.run(g_enhanced_instance)
        ↓
    G_enhanced.meta_learning()
    G_enhanced.few_shot_learning()
    G_enhanced.continual_learning()
    G_enhanced.symbolic_representation()
    G_enhanced.generate_tensors()
        ↓
    CV_Adapt(T_G, T_R, T_LLM, T_DTB) → T_AGI

================================================================================
SECTION 1 — TEXTUAL DESCRIPTION
================================================================================

1.1  MQ FOUNDATION — Moral Quotient Training Signal

The Moral Quotient (MQ) channel in T_G currently derives its score from
computational proxies: continual learning stability and task loss. These
proxies measure consistency and accuracy but carry no inherent moral content.
To ground MQ in a defined moral corpus, the Foundation Initializer extracts
moral reasoning passages from the NIV Scripture text, classifies them by moral
dimension (justice, compassion, integrity, wisdom, accountability, faithfulness),
and builds a reference embedding corpus. This corpus becomes the primary signal
against which MQ scoring is calibrated. When G_enhanced evaluates a task's
moral dimension, it measures proximity to this reference — not proximity to a
computational proxy. The six moral dimensions map directly to the six quotient
channels: MQ is primary, but EQ and SQ are also informed by the compassion and
community dimensions of the corpus.

1.2  TB FOUNDATION — Time-Binding Semantic Memory

The SymbolicMemory module (Time-Binding, Korzybski 1921) accumulates semantic
embeddings of concepts across episodes. In default initialization, memory begins
empty — the first episode binds the first concepts. The Foundation Initializer
pre-populates SymbolicMemory with semantic embeddings derived from Scripture
before any episode runs. This establishes the Word as the foundational semantic
layer. All subsequent concept-binding during task episodes is measured for
density and coherence against a memory that already contains this foundation.
TB_density — the mean cosine similarity across stored embeddings — is therefore
anchored from inception by the coherence of the scriptural semantic space.

1.3  HKS FOUNDATION — Hierarchical Knowledge Structure Root

The HierarchicalKnowledgeStructure (HKS) graph initializes empty by default.
The first task episode creates the first domain node. The Foundation Initializer
pre-constructs the root layer of the HKS graph before any episode runs,
establishing a Scripture-derived knowledge hierarchy as the foundational
structure. Root node: the source corpus itself. Primary domain nodes: the
major knowledge domains present in Scripture (creation, law, wisdom, prophecy,
gospel, epistle). All task-episode domain nodes are subsequently added as
children of this pre-existing structure. HKS_depth is therefore non-zero at
inception and reflects the foundational hierarchy from the first forward pass.

================================================================================
SECTION 2 — COMPUTATION NOTATION
================================================================================

Let:
    C_NIV       = NIV Scripture corpus (full text, tokenized)
    D_moral     = {justice, compassion, integrity, wisdom, accountability, faithfulness}
    D_scripture = {creation, law, wisdom, prophecy, gospel, epistle}

2.1  MQ Foundation

    Extract:
        P_moral = { p ∈ C_NIV : moral_classifier(p) ∈ D_moral }

    Embed:
        E_moral = { embed(p) : p ∈ P_moral }   shape: (|P_moral|, d_embed)

    Index:
        MQ_reference = { d : mean( embed(p) for p ∈ P_moral if class(p) = d )
                         for d ∈ D_moral }
        shape: (6, d_embed)  — one centroid per moral dimension

    Calibrate:
        MQ_score(task) = mean( cosine_sim( embed(task), MQ_reference[d] )
                         for d ∈ D_moral )
        ∈ [0, 1]

2.2  TB Foundation

    Pre-bind:
        For each book b ∈ C_NIV:
            For each passage p ∈ sample(b, n=TB_SEED_PER_BOOK):
                SymbolicMemory.bind( concept = canonical_label(p),
                                     episode_id = -1 )   # -1 = pre-episode

    Result:
        |TB.memory| = |C_NIV_books| × TB_SEED_PER_BOOK   at inception
        TB_density  = mean_cosine_sim( TB.memory )        > 0 at first episode

2.3  HKS Foundation

    Initialize root:
        HKS.graph.add_node( "root::Scripture", level=0, type="root" )

    Add primary domains:
        For each d ∈ D_scripture:
            HKS.graph.add_node( f"domain::{d}", level=1, type="domain" )
            HKS.graph.add_edge( "root::Scripture", f"domain::{d}", weight=1.0 )

    Result:
        HKS.depth   = level_2 / 5.0 = 0.4   at inception (before any task)
        HKS.graph   = pre-structured, ready to receive task nodes as children

================================================================================
SECTION 3 — PYTHON IMPLEMENTATION
================================================================================
"""

import re
import time
import logging
import numpy as np
from dataclasses import dataclass, field
from typing import List, Dict, Optional, Tuple

# ── NIV SCRIPTURE CORPUS (embedded) ─────────────────────────────────────────
import base64 as _b64, gzip as _gz
_NIV_B64 = """"""

def _load_niv_corpus() -> str:
    """Decompress and return the embedded NIV Scripture corpus text."""
    return _gz.decompress(_b64.b64decode(_NIV_B64)).decode("utf-8")
